<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-551-762  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 551 762.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC-Computing  Sept 1989 v2 n9 p66(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A VGA card for the rest of us. (Hercules Computer Technology VGAadapter)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Jerome, Marty.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Hercules Computer Technology Inc. (products).andO;Product:   Hercules Computer Technology VGA Card (Graphics board)(evaluation).andO;Topic:     Computer graphicsGraphics Boards-CardsEvaluation.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>If you've put off upgrading your PC with VGA graphics because you're not adesktop publisher, a CAD user, or a millionaire, Hercules Computer Technologybrings good news: a VGA board for the rest of us.andM;Compatible with IBM's VGA standard (and thus with EGA and CGA), the HerculesVGA makes a welcome entrance at the low end of the price scale with a listprice of $299.andP;  It's an eight-bit card with no switches, jumpers, or softwaredrivers.andP;  Complete installation and testing will take a full 12 minutes.andM;The Hercules VGA works on any IBM-compatible PC, XT, or AT bus, with anyanalog RGB or multifrequency monitor.andP;  with a gracious two-year warranty andunlimited technical support.andM;Its performance proved respectable in tests, but the Hercules VGA will notblind you with its speed.andP;  Nor will it dazzle you with multiple enhancedmodes (it supports industry standard modes only).andP;  If you use graphicsapplications intensively, you'll probably be happier with 16-bit VGA boardsthat handle screen data faster.andP;  But the Hercules VGA is an honest,hassle-free card, a bargain if you're an everyday word processor andspreadsheet user who wants a crisper display with more colors.andM;For more information contact Hercules Computer Technology, in Berkeley,California, at 800-5320600.andO;</TEXT></DOC>